casebody.data:
James D. MCCURRY and Christina E. McCurry, Respondents,
v.
Randolph A. KUHLMAN, Appellant. WD 81980 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. Order filed: April 16, 2019 Robert E. Cowherd, Chillicothe, for Respondents. Trentis E. Miller, Chillicothe, Co-counsel for Respondents. Anthony W. Bonuchi, for Appellant. Before Special Division: Edward R. Ardini, Jr., Presiding Judge, Anthony Rex Gabbert, Judge and Kelly Broniec, Special Judge

ORDER

PER CURIAM:

Randolph Kuhlman appeals the trial court's judgment finding he failed to establish ownership of a parcel of real property by adverse possession, and quieting title of the property in favor of James and Christina McCurry. Finding no error, we affirm. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum of law has been provided to the parties. Rule 84.16(b).
